<br>
Just some mumblings here:<br>
Evade was implimented because rogues were getting hosed before anyone in the group had a chance to catch up in &quot;hate value&quot;.  Essentially, our &quot;hate rate&quot; was higher than anyone else could get close to.  As it was, even being reset to nearly zero hate, a rogue could be back at the top of the hate list in only a matter of a few combat rounds.  Yes it's true, why? Looking back at our &quot;hate rate&quot; we'll see that it increases at about 2x the rate of anyone else's.<br>
<br>
Lets look at Kendrick's &quot;arbitrary number exampple&quot; for a second.<br>
Rogue was at 10k<br>
Warrior was at 5k<br>
Monk was 2.5k <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  (which seems a little low for me but we'll go with it)</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
now for convieniance of numbers we'll break that into 10 &quot;rounds of combat&quot; (assumption is that Kendrick's example reflected ONE evade cycle)<br>
Rate at which hate is gained (hate/round):<br>
Rogue 1000<br>
Warrior 500<br>
Monk 250<br>
<br>
So in our little example, Mr Rogue evades and gets set to 3750 (assuming the evade was sucessful...Mr Rogue was tanking so there was a good chance it wasn't <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :p --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":p"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  )<br>
<br>
Warrior 5000<br>
Rogue 3750<br>
Monk 2500<br>
<br>
now lets advance three (yep 3) combat rounds into the future just to see where everyone is at...<br>
<br>
Rogue 6750<br>
Warrior 6500<br>
monk 3250<br>
<br>
Oh Crap! Mr Rogue is in hot water again! What will he do, I know He'll evade...No wait, he's got 7 more combat rounds before evade cycles.  Crap, pull out the res stick cus Mr Rogue=OWNED.<br>
<br>
Now, lets see if we can suggest a way to fix this while still giving rogues a working evade and VI the change that they're after.<br>
<br>
I think the main idea is to make rogues responsible for their damage and still keep them off the top of the hate list.  Having the hate reset to between #2 &amp; #3 on the list was a valiant attempt but still falls short within a second or two of combat (rather terminally I might add).  One could suggest that you could reset to average between #3 and #4 or even #4 and #5 (on large raids there's actually not much difference in hate values in the top 10 anyway) Oh wait I think I just stumbled on something there too...This change absolutely hoses rogues on multiple group encounters.  Wow, that was shortsighted.  <br>
<br>
Anyhoo...<br>
<br>
The heart of the problem is the &quot;hate increase rate&quot;.  <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>  IF</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> a rogue can sucessfully regain #1 on the hate list significantly before evade cycles, we're dead (cripes and that's assuming no failure).<br>
<br>
Resetting to nearly 0 hate is wrong, I can accept that.  Resetting to between fixed positions on a hate list is wrong too.  How to appropriately handle this is really a tricky problem (it's early here and I still haven't had my second cup of coffee).  I'll have to get back on a possible solution. <p><CENTER><TABLE cellpadding=5 cellspacing=0 border=0 width=100%><TR><TD colspan=2><HR></TD></TR><TR valign=top><TD align=right><FONT Size=5><B><u>Chemistrius Ul'Veldrin   </u></B></FONT><BR><FONT size=-1>55<sup>th</Sup> Season Dark Elf Blackguard<BR>Requiem of Souls</FONT></TD><TD><FONT size=-1>It will be a hard life.<BR>One without remorse, without reward, without regret.<BR>A path will be placed before you, the choice is yours alone.<BR>Do what you think you cannot do.<BR>It will be a hard life, but you will find out who you are.</FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD colspan=2><HR></TD></TR></TABLE></CENTER></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uchemistrius.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Chemistrius</A> at: 2/7/01 8:45:52 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ushadowcross.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Shadowcross</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_purplespot.gif BORDER=0 HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Moderator</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/7/01 8:39:45 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Changes to what we are proposing to Evade +more.</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> The heart of the problem is the &quot;hate increase rate&quot;. IF a rogue can sucessfully regain #1 on the hate list significantly before evade cycles, we're dead (cripes and that's assuming no failure).<br>
