<br>
---<br>
I do want to report one thing that we have already discovered internally about rogues that is broken and will be fixed when we make these changes. Yes, it is a nerf, but not in the true sense of the word.<br>
<br>
In the old days, NPCs had a limited size to their hate-list (basically the way that they track who they are angry at). In those days, evade would just drop you to the bottom of that list. Recently we increased the size of that list dramatically. This allows us to do a lot more with NPCs. But evade was never changed to reflect this, so it still drops you to the bottom of the hate-list. Essentially, this allows a rogue to do significant damage to an opponent, and then with the use of evade, become less 'hated' than someone that has done no damage to the NPC at all, but just has a somewhat negative faction with that NPC and is standing someplace on the other side of the zone. The rogue can then beat the NPC up with impunity. Basically, evade is far too useful for avoiding aggro from an NPC, and we're going to change it to be more in line with its original function.<br>
<br>
---<br>
<br>
Now if the change is to move the rogue to the 2nd spot, does that mean that mobs bedore SoV have a max hatelist of 2 people?<br>
<br>
I am not here arguing if Evade should be nerfed, but only moving from 1st to 2nd on a succesful evade IS a nerf, and very much in the true sence of the word. <p>Ishwar - level 36 Barbarian Rogue</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ukivi.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kivi</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/7/01 8:48:15 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Changes to what we are proposing to Evade +more.</span><hr size=1> Too often in this discussion people assume that evade will work every time it recycles. Well, it can fail five times in a row if you're unlucky and four is not that uncommon. Couple that with the fact that if you have a little lag or if you are in a constant hail of attacks you will get pushed back and "interrupted".<br>
