Basically Evade is being changed for 2 reasons <br>
<br>
One is because of the way the hatelist was changed and the default value of hate we are given is 120 on a successful evade where as just being in agro range is 128 so this creates a problem where after pounding on a mob we're lower on hatelist then a passerby.<br>
<br>
Two is the one Verant isn't really saying in to many words but seems really to be part of it ...Damage accountability,and realing us in a bit. Making us more accountable for the damage we do.<br>
Basically right now we are teatering on the edge of doing to much damage on the edge of being to powerful in melee damage..how do you fix that? <br>
You either nerf the damage output or you make the character more accountable for the damage being delivered.So that if we continue as we were at full out offensiveness we get pounded on more if we backoff a bit and stop attacking inbetween evades to offset this change we as a by product lower our damage output.<br>
<br>
This really seems to be the Why it is being looked at changing in the way that it is.IT makes us like wizards or Necro's ..yes we have the ability to do increadable damage but if we do so recklessly we will be a manasink for heals.<br>
If we holdback some we will do less damage but retain the same control of agro we had before with more accountability for that damage like everyone else has to already.<br>
<br>
Now for the obvious fix that no ones pointed out.(that i've noticed)<br>
The hatelist had 6 spots on it now it has 60 evade was made when there was only 6 and it lowered us to 6th spot and that value was 120hate.<br>
Now with 60 that has the potential of moving us 59 spots down the hatelist..to much.<br>
